      },
      {
        "title": "Parallel Agent Release Automation Pipeline",
        "whats_possible": "You frequently chain version bumps, npm publishes, GitHub releases, README updates, and cross-repo syncs — and friction occurs when steps are forgotten or done out of order. A single prompt can spawn parallel agents handling independent tracks (docs update, version bump across all files, changelog generation) that converge for the final publish step. This could compress your multi-session release process into one autonomous run.",
